RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEAUTIFUL STAR settled three wide, went after the leader on the final turn, was put to urging in the stretch long drive and was up in time nearing the wire. CHICA RABIOSA firmly rated behind the pacesetters, took over when ready at the three eighths pole, rallied clear to the late stages but was nailed nearing the finish. CAGED PIXIE alternated for the advantage inside and began fading on the final turn. NURSE RACHETT earned a narrow lead in the two path, dueled to the far turn and faded. MS BOOMBASTIC stumbled slightly at the start, trailed early and was always far back. LONDONDERRY lacked speed and chased well off the pace and lacked a response.

SEA IMAGE chased along the rail on the backstretch, was taken up sharply into the far turn and had no further response.
